 since Friday found dead, police say</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/wexit-canada-separation-conservatives-1.5638244?cmp=rss" target="_blank">Most Canadians opposed to Wexit, but poll finds new party could pose challenge to Conservatives</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/conservatives-canada-economic-coronavirus-1.5638321?cmp=rss" target="_blank">Financial scrutiny, back-to-work bonus among Conservative demands ahead of fiscal snapshot</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/seattle-protesters-highway-dies-1.5638278?cmp=rss" target="_blank">1 of 2 protesters hit by vehicle on Seattle freeway dies; man, 27, charged with vehicular assault</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/ethiopia-protest-singer-hachalu-hundessa-killed-1.5638219?cmp=rss" target="_blank">Death toll in Ethiopian protests after killing of singer rises to 166</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/newfoundland-labrador/rnc-craigmiller-police-presence-stjohns-1.5638183?cmp=rss" target="_blank">Police investigating suspicious death, maintain presence as St. John&#039;s street reopens</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/schools-virtual-learning-privacy-1.5615999?cmp=rss" target="_blank">Schools urged to ensure students&#039; security and privacy when conducting classes online</a><a class="clip" href="https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/venice-covid-tourism-economy-1.5636741?cmp=rss" target="_blank">A tale of 2 cities: Venice residents torn between mass tourism and a more harmonious existence</a></div></div></div></div>	</div >
